<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALLA BREVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN HENKEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XENAKIS: "Pleiades;" ISHII: Concertante. Les Percussions de Strasbourg; Keiko 
Abe, marimba. 
</P>
<P>
Denon 81757 3678 2 (compact disc). Written for the Strasbourg ensemble, 
Xenakis' four-movement suite explores the gamut of percussion sounds with his 
characteristic mixture of rigorous process and galvanic energy, all pertinently 
and powerfully rapped out here. Maki Ishii's 1988 Concertante for marimba solo 
and six percussionists is a more lyrical effort, with a diffuse, suspended 
sense of time, neatly captured in a performance at once earthy and abstracted. 
JOHN HENKEN 
</P>
</TEXT>
