<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALLA BREVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIMOTHY MANGAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRAHMS: Hungarian Dances. Staatskapelle Berlin conducted by Otmar Suitner. 
Denon 81757 4597 2. 
</P>
<P>
The liner notes state approvingly that "Suitner invariably conducts in an 
orthodox manner without any hint of flashiness . . . " Fine for 16th-Century, 
five-part motets maybe, but a strange thing to brag about in a recording of the 
Hungarian Dances. Generally dense textures, wimpily projected dance rhythms, 
sedate lyricism and a merely adequate orchestra combine to produce this utterly 
ordinary and forgettable release. TIMOTHY MANGAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
