<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP EYE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PATRICK GOLDSTEIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
THIS YEAR'S MODEL: Remember all the publicity George Michael got when he 
announced he wouldn't be doing any videos for his new album (because he wanted 
us to focus on his song lyrics)? Let's say that was . . . half-true. Michael 
isn't appearing in any videos, but that doesn't mean he isn't making any 
videos. 
</P>
<P>
In fact, hot-shot director David Fincher (who's scheduled to shoot "Aliens 
III") has just finished a five-day shoot in London of Michael's upcoming 
single, "Freedom 90." Instead of spotlighting George, the clip showcases a 
quintet of world-class fashion models, including Cindy Crawford, Christy 
Turlington and Tatiana, who lip-sync the song (you could say it's like Robert 
Palmer's "Addicted to Love" clip, except without Palmer). . . . And from our 
Wish We'd Been There Dept.: When Tom Petty celebrated his 40th birthday at his 
San Fernando Valley home last weekend, the music room got quite a workout. 
Celebrants included Bruce Springsteen, Roger McGuinn, Jeff Lynne and most of 
the Heartbreakers, who launched into a spontaneous jam, featuring such 
favorites as "Little Red Rooster," "Roll Over Beethoven," "Mr. Tambourine Man" 
and "Great Balls of Fire." Spectators included Elvis Costello, Gary Shandling, 
Carlene Carter and Howie Epstein (who are a couple these days) and Kathy 
Valentine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, George Michael . . . puts his "faith" in fashion models. BRADFORD 
BRANSON 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
