<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONSIDERING ART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Re Hilary de Vries' Oct. 21 article "All the Rage," about performance artist 
Karen Finley: 
</P>
<P>
The Times has twice quoted the artist -- who smears various substances over her 
partly naked body -- as saying, "I consider good art that which destroys the 
last generation's hopes." 
</P>
<P>
Well, I consider "performance art" to be all performance and no art, unless 
gaining attention and publicity is an art. If so, "Gabor and the Cop" is the 
highest example to date. 
</P>
<P>
It is what those do who have mastered no art whatsoever. 
</P>
<P>
FRED SCIFERS, Downey 
</P>
</TEXT>
