<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHALLENGES TO PORTRAYALS AND CASTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Is it a tribute -- as the makers of "Memphis Belle" say in the credits -- to 
show bomber crew members fighting among themselves in mid-air while leading a 
raid and the co-pilot whining because he is not the skipper and the navigator 
dissolving into tears at the first ack-ack? 
</P>
<P>
And did the fliers really spend their time on the ground shouting and arguing 
and taking night walks to pat the nose of their plane? No wonder Gregory Peck 
had such trouble in "12 O'Clock High." 
</P>
<P>
CYRUS MUNDALL (Ex-member 8th Air Force), Hollywood 
</P>
</TEXT>
