<HEADLINE>
<P>
RESTAURANTS; 
</P>
<P>
SLIPPING IN QUIETLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
These restaurants have all opened recently without much fanfare. 
</P>
<P>
Dale's Bistro, 361 N. La Cienega Blvd., Los Angeles. (213) 659-3996. Style: 
Nouveau nostalgia, '90s style. 
</P>
<P>
Setting: Spartan. Recommended: Onion soup with three cheeses; roasted chicken 
with herbes de Provence and mustard; duck rillettes. Cost per person: $12-$20. 
</P>
<P>
Flora Kitchen, 460 S. La Brea Ave., Los Angeles. (213) 931-9900. Style: 
Likeable cafe and takeout where the peoplewatching is almost as good as the 
menu. Setting: Post-modern cafe with clean lines and beautiful flowers. 
Recommended: Cornish game hen, breast of chicken sandwich; apple pie. Cost per 
person: $8-$12. 
</P>
<P>
North Beach Bar &amp; Grill, 111 Rose Ave., Venice. (213) 399-3900. Style: 
Macho meals for low cholesterol counts. Setting: An unfussy '40s feel. 
Recommended: Oysters Rockefeller; filet steak; beer-batter shrimp. Cost per 
person: $15-$35. 
</P>
<P>
Mango Reef, 8751 W. Pico Blvd., Los Angeles. (213) 271-7887. Style: Formerly 
Sugar Shack, now reopened with plastic surgery. Setting: Tropical and colorful. 
Recommended: Caesar salad; shrimp cocktail; tostada. Cost per person: $8-$15. 
</P>
<P>
O'toto, 7119 Melrose Ave., Los Angeles. (213) 937-5435. Style: Adventures in 
eclecticism, Pacific rim style. Setting: Zen-minimalist. Recommended: Goat 
cheese flan with grilled Japanese eggplant; Thai papaya salad with fresh 
shrimp; beef tongue with epazote black beans. Cost per person: $12-$30. Kathie 
Jenkins 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Drawing, TED ENGELBART 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
