<P>
FALLING CONCRETE KILLS 6 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HONG KONG 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Six people were crushed to death in Hong Kong and five were injured when a 
concrete building ledge crashed to the pavement, police said Saturday. It took 
firefighters about an hour to free those trapped beneath the 32-yard-long, 
3-yard-wide ledge after it fell from an industrial building on the Kowloon 
peninsula Friday evening. 
</P>
