<P>
COMMUNIST LEADER SURVIVES SCANDAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The revamped East German Communist Party, fighting to survive a financial 
scandal, voted to keep Gregor Gysi as its leader but moved to give up its 
controversial property holdings. The arrest of two senior members of the 
renamed Party of Democratic Socialism for diverting $71 million in party funds 
to accounts in Moscow has dealt a severe blow to the party's new reformist 
image. The scandal also appears likely to hurt the party's chances in elections 
for an all-German parliament on Dec. 2. 
</P>
