<HEADLINE>
<P>
OCC RETURNS INTERCEPTION 98 YARDS, WINS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COSTA MESA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It wasn't a record, but Lawrence Hatch's 98-yard interception return for a 
touchdown changed the momentum in Orange Coast College's 24-19 victory over 
Saddleback in a Mission Conference football game Saturday at OCC. 
</P>
<P>
Hatch, a sophomore defensive back, was a yard short of the OCC record. Mike 
Lacy (1973) and Bill Craft (1986) each returned interceptions 99 yards for 
touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
Hatch's interception occurred with Orange Coast leading, 10-7, but Saddleback 
was driving. On second and five at the OCC 16, Hatch stepped in front of a 
Saddleback receiver and caught the ball. He started up the middle, then cut to 
the left sideline and ran nearly untouched into the end zone. 
</P>
<P>
Orange Coast scored later in the second quarter to take a 24-7 halftime lead. 
Saddleback scored a touchdown in the each of the final two quarters, the last 
with 52 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback quarterback Jeff Bailey completed a 28-yard scoring pass to Terry 
Isles, but the two-point conversion pass fell incomplete. Saddleback's onside 
kick went out of bounds at the OCC 37, and the Pirates ran out the clock. 
</P>
<P>
"Our defense made some big plays," OCC Coach Bill Workman said. "We stayed 
conservative the second half and played the clock some. We won, and that's what 
is important." 
</P>
<P>
OCC (5-2, 4-2) was coming off a 43-15 loss to Rancho Santiago in which the 
Pirates turned the ball over seven times. They turned the ball over only twice 
against Saddleback, both on interceptions by Mike Miller. 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback's four-game winning streak was stopped. Each team is 1-1 in Central 
Division play. 
</P>
<P>
OCC took the opening kickoff and drove to the Saddleback 16 but settled for a 
31-yard field goal by Mike Wade. 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback (4-3, 4-2) came back with a 14-play, 82-yard scoring drive that 
ended on a two-yard dive by Matt Carvalho that made it 7-3. 
</P>
<P>
OCC quarterback Greg Angelovic then led a 58-yard drive that he capped with a 
four-yard run for a touchdown to give OCC a 10-7 lead with 12:10 left in the 
half. Hatch's interception came at 10:47. 
</P>
<P>
OCC scored its final touchdown on a one-yard run by Jim Warren with 3:49 left 
to take a 24-7 lead. Angelovic was 11 for 16 for 173 yards, and his favorite 
targets were tight ends Derek Whiddon and Mark Rapp. Whiddon had six catches 
for 81 yards and Rapp had two for 53 yards. 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback's Chi Chi Biehn scored on a one-yard run with 2:21 left in the third 
quarter, but the extra-point attempt by Scott Hannah was wide and OCC led, 
24-13. 
</P>
<P>
Bailey was 18 for 31 for 210 yards, but three passes were intercepted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
