<HEADLINE>
<P>
'MERCI TRAIN' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am researching the French "Merci Train" of 1949, composed of 48 boxcars sent 
to the United States from France after World War II. 
</P>
<P>
The cars were filled with gifts and designated to be delivered in each state. 
</P>
<P>
I am trying to locate people who remember the train, its arrival in the United 
States and what has become of the boxcars and gifts. More important, I am 
looking for information on the sentiment in France leading to the gesture of 
thanks. 
</P>
<P>
All credits will be given. 
</P>
<P>
JULIE CHRISTINE 
</P>
<P>
417 Yorktown No. 6 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach, CA 92648 
</P>
