<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: SAN MARINO; 
</P>
<P>
SON'S WORK SCUTTLES PERMIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 16-year-old's home business has scuttled his mother's bid to enlarge her 
house -- at least temporarily. 
</P>
<P>
The Planning Commission on Wednesday refused to hear Gayle Young's request for 
an expansion permit because Young's son, Joseph, 16, runs a mail-order business 
from the home without a license. 
</P>
<P>
City Manager John Nowak said the city will try to resolve the matter 
informally. Meanwhile, Young's request for expansion will be heard next month. 
</P>
<P>
Joseph Young, who calls his business "Prime Opportunities," sends out 
literature on ways to earn money. His mother said she didn't know a license was 
required for his endeavor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
