<HEADLINE>
<P>
FADE TO BLACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For the TV viewers who prefer to see the classic movies in black-and-white, the 
solution is very simple. Just turn the color knob on your TV set to the extreme 
off position. Presto, instant black and white! I tried it the other night on a 
colorized classic and it worked great. 
</P>
<P>
Randolph C. Andrews, Laguna Hills 
</P>
